---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'June 18, 2026';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Privacy Policy', url: '/privacy/' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — WrenchStack"
  description="How WrenchStack collects, uses, and protects information. We use privacy-friendly cookieless analytics by default and Google Analytics only with your consent; we never sell personal data and only collect what you choose to send us."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-orange-600">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <p>
        WrenchStack ("WrenchStack," "we," "us") is an independent research publication covering
        software and service vendors for trades and field-service businesses. This policy explains what
        information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have. We keep our data practices
        deliberately minimal.
      </p>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>By default we use <strong>privacy-friendly, cookieless analytics</strong> (Cloudflare Web Analytics) — no personal profiles, no cross-site tracking.</li>
        <li>We load <strong>Google Analytics only if you accept</strong> our cookie banner — and you can decline or withdraw consent at any time.</li>
        <li>We only collect personal information you <strong>choose to send us</strong> (e.g., when you email us or submit a form).</li>
        <li>We <strong>never sell</strong> your personal information.</li>
        <li>We don't run user accounts, and we don't operate a newsletter at this time.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <h3>1. Analytics data</h3>
      <p>
        By default we use <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a>,
        a privacy-first tool that <strong>does not use cookies</strong> and does not collect personal or
        identifiable information. It reports aggregate metrics only — page views, referring sites, country, and
        device type — and we cannot identify individual visitors from it.
      </p>
      <p>
        With your consent, we also use <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Analytics 4</a>
        (provided by Google) to understand traffic in more detail. Google Analytics <strong>sets cookies</strong>, so it
        is loaded <strong>only after you click "Accept" on our cookie banner</strong>; if you decline, it is never loaded
        and no analytics cookies are set. We enable IP anonymization and do not use Google Analytics advertising or
        remarketing features.
      </p>
      <h3>2. Information you provide</h3>
      <p>
        If you contact us by email or submit a form (for example, the vendor-submission form), we receive the
        information you choose to include — typically your name, email address, and your message. Form
        submissions are processed by <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Web3Forms</a>
        and delivered to our inbox. We use this only to respond to you.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and your choices</h2>
      <p>
        By default, WrenchStack sets <strong>no analytics or advertising cookies</strong> — our default analytics
        (Cloudflare Web Analytics) are cookieless. If you click <strong>"Accept"</strong> on our cookie banner, Google
        Analytics sets its own cookies to measure traffic (with IP anonymization). If you click <strong>"Decline,"</strong>
        no analytics cookies are set. Your choice is remembered in your browser, and you can change it at any time:
      </p>
      <p>
        <button id="reset-consent" type="button" class="rounded-md border border-slate-300 bg-white px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 no-underline hover:bg-slate-50">Manage cookie preferences</button>
      </p>
      <p>
        Separately, WrenchStack earns affiliate commissions on some outbound links (see our
        <a href="/disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a>). When you click an affiliate link and leave our site, the
        destination vendor or its affiliate network (for example, PartnerStack) may set its own cookies to attribute
        the referral. Those cookies are governed by the destination's privacy policy, not ours, and we do not control
        or have access to them.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to questions, corrections, and vendor inquiries you send us.</li>
        <li>To understand, in aggregate, which content is useful so we can improve it.</li>
        <li>To detect and prevent abuse of the site.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>We rely on a small number of service providers, each with its own privacy policy:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosting, content delivery, security, and cookieless Web Analytics.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> (Google LLC) — consent-based, cookie-using site analytics, loaded only if you accept.</li>
        <li><strong>Web3Forms</strong> — processing form submissions.</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate networks and vendors</strong> — only when you click an outbound affiliate link and leave our site.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we do not do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information.</li>
        <li>We do not build advertising profiles or run third-party ad networks.</li>
        <li>We do not share the contents of your messages except as needed to respond to you.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have rights under laws such as the EU/UK GDPR or the California
        Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) — including the right to access, correct, or delete personal information we
        hold about you, and the right to know that we do not sell it. Because we collect so little, in most cases
        the only personal data we hold is an email thread you started. To exercise any right, email
        <a href="mailto:hello@wrenchstack.com">hello@wrenchstack.com</a> and we'll act on it.
      </p>

      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain email and form correspondence only as long as needed to handle your request and keep a
        reasonable record, then delete it. Cloudflare Web Analytics contains no personal data. Google Analytics
        data, when you've consented to it, is retained according to Google's data-retention settings and used only
        in aggregate for trend analysis.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        WrenchStack is a business-to-business publication and is not directed at children. We do not knowingly
        collect personal information from anyone under 16.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy as our practices or the law evolve. Material changes will be reflected in the
        "Last updated" date above.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy or your data? Email
        <a href="mailto:hello@wrenchstack.com">hello@wrenchstack.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>

  <script>
    // "Manage cookie preferences": clear the stored consent choice and reload, which
    // re-shows the consent banner (see Layout.astro). Harmless while analytics is inactive.
    document.getElementById('reset-consent')?.addEventListener('click', function () {
      try { localStorage.removeItem('ws-analytics-consent'); } catch (e) {}
      location.reload();
    });
  </script>
</Layout>
